description:
A dashboard for visualizing results from the k6.io load testing tool, using the InfluxDB exporter.

inspire from https://grafana.com/dashboards/2587 & k6 cloud dashboard.

simple & informative dashboard

targets.query:
from(bucket: "myfirstinfluxdbbucket")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "http_reqs")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "value")
  |> group(columns: ["_measurement", "_field"])
  |> aggregateWindow(every: ${interval_value}s, fn: sum, createEmpty: false)
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with _value: r._value / float(v: ${interval_value}) }))
  |> yield(name: "rate_per_second")

from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "http_req_duration")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._field == "value")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r.expected_response == "true")
  |> group(columns: ["_measurement", "_field"])
  |> aggregateWindow(every: ${interval_value}s, fn: max, createEmpty: false)
  |> yield(name: "max")

from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "http_reqs" and r._field == "value" and r.status != "200" and r.status != "201")

  |> aggregateWindow(every: ${interval_value}s, fn: sum, createEmpty: false)
  |> yield(name: "sum")

//SELECT count(*),"status" from (SELECT "method", "value", "status" FROM "http_req_duration" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY "name","status" )

from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "http_req_duration" and r._field == "value")
  |> group(columns: ["status", "name"])
  |> count()
  |> group(columns: ["status"])

//SELECT percentile("value", 95) as PERCENTILE_95, percentile("value", 99) as PERCENTILE_99, max("value") as  max_response_time, mean("value") as  avg_response_time, min("value") as  min_response_time, count("value") as  count    FROM "http_req_duration" WHERE $timeFilter  GROUP BY "name","status","method"  fill(null)

data = from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "http_req_duration" and r._field == "value")
  |> group(columns: ["status", "name", "method"])

p95 = data
  |> quantile(q: 0.95, method: "estimate_tdigest")
  |> set(key: "_stat", value: "p95")

p99 = data
  |> quantile(q: 0.99, method: "estimate_tdigest")
  |> set(key: "_stat", value: "p99")

maxVal = data
  |> max()
  |> set(key: "_stat", value: "max")

meanVal = data
  |> mean()
  |> set(key: "_stat", value: "mean")

minVal = data
  |> min()
  |> set(key: "_stat", value: "min")

union(tables: [p95, p99, maxVal, meanVal, minVal])
  |> pivot(rowKey:["name"], columnKey: ["_stat"], valueColumn: "_value")
  |> keep(columns: ["name", "p95", "p99", "max", "mean", "min"])

from(bucket: v.bucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "http_reqs" and r._field == "value" and r.status != "200" and r.status != "201")
  |> group(columns: ["_measurement", "_field", "status", "method", "name"])
  |> rename(columns: {_measurement: "Sum"})
  |> aggregateWindow(every: ${interval_value}s, fn: sum, createEmpty: false)
  |> yield(name: "sum")
